column5: Thanks for the reply guys, it was a great moment for me and I cant wait to boat another one.  Mike, the old PB was 44". Phil, who you calling little Lew and Mike, Thanks for the compliments, and Lew I just held the net and you guided her in to it  Can't wait to get out again, Corey
a very fine fish for sure!  congrats!
Well done!!! Congrats on the PB!
What a beauty! Congrats! One of many big ones to come for you by the sounds of it.

Went down to southern Ontario for a weekend of muskie fishing.  Yesterday the rod went off again i grabbed it and after a good fight i got a beauty ski into the net...    Got a quick measurment of her... She measured up to 46.5" inches, that means its a new PB, so here she is...    Back you go big girl...    As you can tell by pics it was pretty darn cold, but not as cold as the water was... Oh well it was all worth it!  Hope to get down there again, Corey
I have been waiting for this report!  awesome fish man,
Nice musky !!!!.  .congrats on your new PB...cheers
I've already told you once today Corey, but it's worth repeating, congrats on the PB  Your getting to be a pretty darned good musky fisherman !!
WTG Corey!!!!!!!!!!  A beauty fish! I'm happy for ya! Thanks for showing us.
Congrats on your PB musky  Rob
WTG on the ski. A very healthy looking fish.
Congradulations!!! what was the old PB?
Corey , she is a beauty!!!! congrats mang
That's a really fine looking musky Doesn't look like it's from the Kawarthas making it a more difficult catch. Congrats, ehg
Congrats, she's a real beauty.
A very fine PB Musky Corey!!!  Congrats Bubba!!!
Congratulations!  Beauty fish
Congrats. Is that a lake St.Clair fish? Looks kinda spotted like a St. Clair ski.
Well done little man!
Nice one, congrats...
Nice looking ski and congrats on your PB!!...they sure look different down there compared to the olive green ones here on the Ottawa R.

For those of you that don't know Corey (mistyjr1) he's only 15 years old but is one of the finest fishermen I've had the pleasure of sharing my boat with and is as good or even better than some of those I've fished with who are are many  many years  older than him.  Corey and I have fished together a few times on the West Arm of Nippissing and he's excellent with a net on big fish...... (he netted the one on my avatar) ..........and as I said above, he's also becoming pretty darned good at catching muskies too and I think were all gonna see some very impressive fish come from this young angler in the years to come.  Lookin forward to netting a biggun for you at Lakair next August Corey
werd lew.  he's also got some of the hugest legs i've ever seen.  congrats Corey!  pretty sure thats a mountsberg fish.
Congrats, nice healthy girth on that one too!
Way to go Corey, beautiful fish.  Congrats on the new PB.  Joey

Awesome catch Corey you must have been pumped when you saw this big girl congratz on the new PB.  You and your Dad seem to have a great season going for you this year and the season is not even over yet cool.  Lew I must agree with you I have had the pleasure of fishing with Jim and Corey and he sure is a great guy to fish with and at 15 he knows alot and seems very eager to learn. I also cant wait for next Aug to get out again.
Great report and pics Corey  Congratulation on your PB  Beauty of a ski.... nice and clean Thanks for sharing Leechman
nice going  next 50 plus.....LOL
Awesome catch ,Congrats on the PB Cory  Great lookin ski,lookin forward to your next PB     Streamerguy
